CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) — A West Virginia solar power facility has received regulatory approval.The state Public Service Commission granted a siting certificate to Capon Bridge Solar LLC in Hampshire County.Capon Bridge plans to build a 20 megawatt solar generating facility, which will connect with existing distribution facilities owned by Potomac Edison, the commission said Monday in a news release. Construction costs for the project are estimated to be $17 million.The West Virginia Building and Construction Trades Council, AFL-CIO was granted intervenor status in the case. The statement said the commission received no protest to the project’s application, which was widely supported by the community.